1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,175
Stop scrolling, I need to talk to you about AI art.

2
00:00:03,175 --> 00:00:08,812
If you’re seeing smooth lighting and perfect textures everywhere, you’re stuck on the Visual Plateau.

3
00:00:08,812 --> 00:00:11,887
Everything looks identical and commoditized.

4
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:15,137
My system, Studio OS, needs a fingerprint.

5
00:00:15,137 --> 00:00:19,812
We can’t just be *generated*; we need to look *engineered* and maybe a little bit *broken*.

6
00:00:19,812 --> 00:00:22,625
So, we dumped the mainstream generators.

7
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:29,612
Instead of tuning more diffusion models, I went hunting the deepest corners of GitHub looking for rarity, not scale.

8
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:34,100
We just integrated AlexEidt/ASCII-Video into our pipeline.

9
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:39,025
This thing translates motion and depth into incredibly detailed text streams.

10
00:00:39,025 --> 00:00:42,825
It forces true black and white contrast onto the output.

11
00:00:42,825 --> 00:00:47,462
If you want visual uniqueness, stop perfecting photorealism.

12
00:00:47,462 --> 00:00:49,925
Start building intentional glitch.

